===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|hoop|lang=enm}}, {{term|hoope|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|hōp||mound, raised land", in combination, also "circular object}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*hōpą||bend, bow, arch}} (compare Dutch {{term|hoep|lang=nl}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*kāb-||to bend}} (compare Lithuanian {{term|kabė||hook|lang=lt}}, Old Church Slavic {{term|||tr=kǫpŭ|hill, island|lang=cu}}). More at {{l|en|camp}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A circular [[band]] of metal used to [[bind]] a [[barrel]].
